Defence lawyer Vivek Sharma today called for the defendants to be given life in prison - the most lenient sentence possible - and said that the different roles each of them played in the crime should be taken into account.

He said that judges should not be 'bloodthirsty', adding: 'You can't give capital punishment on demand.'

