One of the other suspects apparently committed suicide while in prison, and a 17-year-old boy convicted of 
involvement in the attack was sentenced to three years in prison.

Speaking outside court yesterday, the 
father of the victim said: 'Now the court has held them guilty, we want them hanged. 
We expect nothing else but the death sentence.'

As the men were told the verdicts in the courtroom, chants of 'hang them' could be heard echoing outside.

One of the four is to launch an appeal over his conviction claiming he was simply driving the bus when the attack took place and was unaware of what was happening inside.

